# VRoid material names

## Source vs workflow

| | Example |
|---|---------|
| **Source** (VRoid import, until Phase B) | `N00_000_00_Face_00_SKIN (Instance)` |
| **Workflow** (pipeline scripts) | `Face.Skin` |

Phase B stores `scene["vroid_material_rename_map"]` (`source → workflow`).

## Standardization rule

1. Strip `N{xx}_{xxx}_{slot}_` import prefix and ` (Instance)`
2. VRoid `_00_` is a **category separator** → replace with `.` + Title Case
3. `_00_FACE` category → `{Feature}.Face` (e.g. `FaceMouth` → `Mouth.Face`). `_00_EYE` → `{Feature}.Eye` (e.g. `EyeIris_00_EYE` → `Iris.Eye`, `EyeHighlight_00_EYE` → `EyeHighlight.Eye`). Other: `Face_00_SKIN` → `Face.Skin`
4. Clothing `_01_CLOTH` → `{Item}.Cloth`; layered → `{ItemAlias}_{NN}.Cloth` (e.g. `Hoodie_01.Cloth`)

